b'\xe2\x80\x9cIs this a state container or a state manager?\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cIs my app isomorphic or universal\xe2\x80\x9d. Guys, stop inventing names, you\xe2\x80\x99re not Adam and Eve.'
b'I participate in both JS and Scala communities, and while some topics may appear harder in Scala, at least I know WHAT I know and what not.'
b'Things can (must?) be \xe2\x80\x9cdumbed down\xe2\x80\x9d with concrete examples and applications, but keeping the formalism in mind helps in not getting lost.'
b'It\xe2\x80\x99s the lack of precision that keeps newcomers from grasping a topic, not the contrary.'
b'Learning new things is way harder if people keep re-inventing \xe2\x80\x9cfriendly\xe2\x80\x9d way of talking about the same thing.'
b'Especially when I\xe2\x80\x99m new to something, I am grateful to people who use formal and precise definitions. It makes it easer to look them up.'
b'Sometimes I hear people complaining about too much \xe2\x80\x9cmath-lingo\xe2\x80\x9d in FP contexts. I\xe2\x80\x99m perplexed, why is it a bad thing?'
